        <p>When you capture an image, you do so using a profile, which is a collection of settings that are applied to the image in advance. Among other things, a profile lets you select a location for a captured image file, apply a specific kind of border to it, set the DPI (dots per inch), and even resize it automatically. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="CaptureGuides.CaptureCreatingImagesGuide,General.OnlineLive">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Profiles/About_Profiles.htm">About Profiles</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:snippetText src="../ForMoreInfo/SeeOnlineHelpOrCreatingImagesGuide.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="CaptureGuides.CaptureGettingStartedGuide" /></p>
